statements: SELECT * FROM genetic_variations ORDER BY gene_name DESC
SELECT gene_name, chromosome_number FROM genetic_variations WHERE population_frequency > 0.5
SELECT id, gene_name, variation_type FROM genetic_variations WHERE chromosome_number = 5
SELECT chromosome_number, variation_type FROM genetic_variations WHERE gene_name = 'BRCA1'
SELECT gene_name, population_frequency FROM genetic_variations ORDER BY population_frequency ASC
SELECT * FROM genetic_variations WHERE variation_type = 'SNP';
SELECT gene_name, population_frequency FROM genetic_variations ORDER BY population_frequency DESC;
SELECT gene_name, chromosome_number FROM genetic_variations WHERE chromosome_number % 2 = 0;
SELECT * FROM genetic_variations WHERE gene_name LIKE 'A%';
SELECT DISTINCT variation_type FROM genetic_variations ORDER BY variation_type ASC;
SELECT * FROM PopulationGeneticVariations;
SELECT population_id, genetic_variation_id, allele FROM PopulationGeneticVariations ORDER BY frequency DESC;
SELECT gene_name, chromosome, position FROM GenomicData WHERE chromosome = 'X';
SELECT genetic_variation_id, gene_name, position FROM GenomicData WHERE position BETWEEN 1000 AND 2000;
SELECT * FROM PopulationGeneticVariations INNER JOIN GenomicData ON PopulationGeneticVariations.genetic_variation_id = GenomicData.genetic_variation_id;
SELECT * FROM PopulationGeneticVariations WHERE frequency > 0.5 ORDER BY population_id DESC;
SELECT gene_name, chromosome, position FROM GenomicData WHERE chromosome='X' AND nucleotide_change LIKE '%A%' ORDER BY position ASC;
SELECT DISTINCT population_id FROM PopulationGeneticVariations WHERE allele='A' OR allele='T';

SELECT genetic_variation_id, gene_name, frequency FROM PopulationGeneticVariations JOIN GenomicData ON PopulationGeneticVariations.genetic_variation_id = GenomicData.genetic_variation_id WHERE position >= 1000 ORDER BY frequency DESC;

SELECT population_id, allele, frequency FROM PopulationGeneticVariations WHERE population_id IN (SELECT population_id FROM PopulationGeneticVariations GROUP BY population_id HAVING COUNT(population_id) > 1) ORDER BY frequency ASC;
SELECT * FROM Population;
SELECT name, genetic_variation FROM Population ORDER BY name DESC;
SELECT base_pair_sequence, base_pair_end FROM GenomicData WHERE chromosome_number = 1;
SELECT result_type FROM AnalysisResults WHERE genomic_data_id = 5;
SELECT * FROM GenomicData ORDER BY base_pair_start ASC, base_pair_end DESC;
SELECT * FROM Population WHERE genetic_variation LIKE 'A%'
SELECT name, genetic_variation FROM Population WHERE id IN (1, 3, 5)
SELECT p.name, a.result_type FROM Population p INNER JOIN GenomicData g ON p.id = g.population_id INNER JOIN AnalysisResults a ON g.id = a.genomic_data_id WHERE g.chromosome_number = 2
SELECT DISTINCT p.name, g.base_pair_sequence FROM Population p INNER JOIN GenomicData g ON p.id = g.population_id WHERE g.base_pair_start BETWEEN 10000 AND 20000
SELECT COUNT(*) AS total_analysis_results FROM AnalysisResults WHERE result_type = 'SNP'
SELECT * FROM population_genes;
SELECT gene_id, gene_name FROM population_genes ORDER BY gene_id DESC;
SELECT gene_name, gene_sequence FROM population_genes WHERE population_id = 1;
SELECT variation_description, variation_type FROM gene_variations WHERE gene_id = 2;
SELECT population_name, country, region FROM population_data WHERE region = 'Europe';
SELECT * FROM gene_variations WHERE gene_id = 1;
SELECT gene_name, gene_sequence FROM population_genes WHERE population_id = 5;
SELECT gene_variations.variation_description, population_data.country FROM gene_variations JOIN population_data ON gene_variations.gene_id = population_data.population_id;
SELECT population_data.population_name, gene_variations.variation_type FROM population_data, gene_variations WHERE population_data.region = 'Europe' AND gene_variations.variation_type = 'insertion';
SELECT * FROM population_genotypes ORDER BY genotype DESC;
SELECT * FROM Population;
SELECT population_name, population_id FROM Population WHERE population_id = 1;
SELECT individual_name, individual_id FROM Individual WHERE individual_id = 10;
SELECT * FROM GenomicData ORDER BY data_id DESC;
SELECT gene_name, variant_name FROM Genes ORDER BY gene_id, variant_id;
SELECT * FROM Population;
SELECT population_name FROM Population WHERE population_id = 1;
SELECT variant_name, gene_name FROM Variant JOIN Genes ON Variant.variant_id = Genes.variant_id;
SELECT Genes.gene_name, GenomicData.genome_data FROM Genes LEFT JOIN GenomicData ON Genes.variant_id = GenomicData.genomic_data_id;
SELECT Individual.individual_name, Population.population_name FROM Individual JOIN Population ON Individual.population_id = Population.population_id;
